# Editorial Domain

**Owns:** assignments, writer tools, SEO/medical review, schedule/publish, writer payments, public articles/specialists.  
**Does not own:** SKU inventory, Creator Collective bids.

## ArticleStatus (Prisma — enforce in `ArticlesService.transition` / publish)

`ASSIGNED → DRAFT → SEO_REVIEW → MEDICAL_REVIEW → APPROVED → SCHEDULED → PUBLISHED`  
Also: `CHANGES_REQUESTED`. Illegal jump → domain error (`409`/`400`) + stable `code`.

## Publish invariants (code anchors)

| Rule | Where |
|---|---|
| Public reads only `PUBLISHED` | `PublishingService.getPublicBySlug` / `listPublic` |
| Publish only from `APPROVED` or `SCHEDULED` | `assertPublishable` → `NOT_APPROVED` |
| If `medicalGateRequired` | history must include `MEDICAL_REVIEW` or `MEDICAL_GATE_REQUIRED` |
| Writers cannot self-approve SEO/medical | role checks on transition endpoints |
| Schedule → publish | `processDueSchedules` / scanner — not browser-only hope |
| On publish | upsert `WriterPayment` PENDING + audit `article.published` |

```typescript
// publishing.service.ts — do not weaken this
if (article.medicalGateRequired) {
  const passed = article.statusHistory.some((h) => h.status === ArticleStatus.MEDICAL_REVIEW);
  if (!passed) throw new ForbiddenException({ code: 'MEDICAL_GATE_REQUIRED', … });
}
```

## Writer payouts

`POST …/writer-payments/:id/release` — `@Roles('FINANCE', 'SUPER_ADMIN')`.  
Only `PENDING` + article `PUBLISHED` → `RELEASED`; audit `writer_payment.released`. Re-release of non-PENDING → `NOT_PENDING` (idempotent-safe refusal).

## Specialists ≠ creators

`SpecialistProfile` is editorial/medical attribution on articles. Never reuse Creator Collective models, routes, or `data-theme="creator"` for specialists. Public blog/articles stay Soft Gift (`gift`).
